cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL

This paper deals with video analysis and specifically with highlight detection, which is a task related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes an unsupervised solution that exploits video duration, which is a signal related to multimedia analysis and mining, suggesting that cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely category. The paper also mentions the use of a ranking framework, which is a technique related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) in the context of hashtagged Instagram videos, which could also suggest cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a possible category.
